               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_1072_Tibb-item1">
                     <author key="person_f4896">
                        <persName type="supplied" subtype="aut">ʾIbrāhīm al-Kīshīإبراهيم الكيشي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7756">Means to Arrive at the Questions about the Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7756">Commentary on Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7756">وسائل الوصول إلى مسائل الفصول</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="alt" key="work_7756">Wasāʼl al-Wuṣūl ilā Masāʼil al-Fuṣūl.</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in Egyptian National Library.</note>
                     <note>This is a collection of <persName type="supplied" key="person_f5647">‘Abd al-Raḥmān al-Ṭabīb</persName> ’s glosses (ḥawāshi) on <persName type="supplied" key="person_f5685">‘Izz al-Dīn Ibrāhīm al-Kīshī</persName> ’s commentary on the Hippocratic Aphorisms. The introduction begins on <locus from="f.151b">f. 151b</locus>; the beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk1: <locus>151b</locus>; Bk2: <locus>156b</locus>; Bk3: <locus>163a</locus>; Bk4: <locus>170b</locus>; Bk5: <locus>177b</locus>; Bk6: <locus>183a</locus>; Bk7: <locus>187a</locus>. Since it is a gloss, it is not clear whether it contains all of al-Kīshī’s text.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
